create a pluralistic political system in the republic 
this has put it at odds with serbia the largest of yugoslavias 
six republics where communist leaders are opposed to any form of 
pluralism 
numerous independent political movements and opposition parties 
including the social democratic and christian democratic parties 
have been established in slovenia and are preparing to compete in 
the regions first free legislative elections scheduled for march 
the decision to implement radical reforms makes it 
possible for slovenes to be proud ribicic said 
croatia yugoslavias secondlargest republic has also 
announced that free elections will be held next spring 
only the leadership of serbia has remained consistently opposed 
to pluralism last month serbias central republic broke off all 
business and government ties with slovenia over their political 
differences 
